HEADWORD: marginal cost of production
<hw>marginal cost of production</hw></mhw>
<pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Economics)</fld> <def>The increase in total cost of
production as a result of producing one more unit of output; since
certain overhead costs are fixed, the <ex>marginal cost</ex> is almost
always less than the total per-unit cost of production averaged over all
units produced.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> incremental cost, differential cost.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Marginalia</ent>⟦br⟧
